article.description: — Ziggy Reid tied his season high with 20 points as Merrimack topped Central Connecticut 66-57 on Saturday.
article.headline: Reid leads Merrimack past Central Connecticut 66-57
article.linkText: Reid leads Merrimack past Central Connecticut 66-57
article.story: NEW BRITAIN, Conn. -- — Ziggy Reid tied his season high with 20 points as Merrimack topped Central Connecticut 66-57 on Saturday. Mikey Watkins had 17 points and six rebounds for Merrimack (8-8, 3-0 Northeast Conference), which won its fourth straight game. Jordan Minor added 8 points and eight blocks. Ian Krishnan had 18 points for the Blue Devils (4-12, 1-2). Nigel Scantlebury added 13 points and six rebounds. Andre Snoddy had eight rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
